sec.p:
Within this study, there was a requirement to deliver an array of synthetic jet actuators (SJAs) to augment high-lift system effectiveness in a wind tunnel model. The key design challenge was producing an array that would meet reduced volume installation constraints in the model envelope without a loss in peak jet exit velocity. The baseline case for comparison was taken to be the authors’ SJA array developed for a leading edge droop model,5 which generated peak jet velocities of ∼90 m/s within a more relaxed geometric configuration. The aim of this study was to:


devise a strategy to design a SJA array for volume-constrained implementation;

provide proper SJA systems wiring for model installation;

implement a basic SJA health monitoring system.

The specific constraints of the present design methodology make it applicable for designing SJA arrays for:


actuator design based on the inclined opposite SJA configuration with circular orifice;

piezoelectric-based diaphragms;

flow separation control applications.
